{"title": "Wish Upon a Shooting Star", "content": "Your wish is its command.\n\nWishing upon seeing a shooting star shooting through the night sky is an old and common custom. Ancient civilizations thought those were the spirits of the departed and that these could bring your wishes to the heavens, so they could be granted. Nowadays, knowledge of the true nature of these falling \"stars\" as meteorites that, instead of going into the heavens, are falling straight towards the Earth, did absolutely nothing to deter this tradition's popularity, and it remains quite common to hear about wishing for something when a shooting star is seen.\n\nAs such, this trope is rather common in fiction, and one of the most recurring ways for characters to Make a Wish along with the Wishing Wells and the Genie in a Bottle.\n\nSubtrope to Make a Wish. See also Cosmic Motifs.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WishUponAShootingStar", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Miitopia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Pinocchio", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CuteHighEarthDefenseClubLove", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TheMysteriousCitiesOfGold", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/IceAgeCollisionCourse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/LiloAndStitch", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LooneyTunesBackInAction", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/StarDarlings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/The100", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DisneyChannel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheSuiteLifeOfZackAndCody", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HannahMontana", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CoryInTheHouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Seinfeld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AnimalCrossing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Miitopia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Okami", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PaperMario", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PaperMarioStickerStar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/PaperMarioColorSplash", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php